					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex; Sefardi square script of c14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex. </support>
								<extent>126 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>315</height>
										<width>250</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>245</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>126 folios (+ 2 unfoliated folios at the beginning and at the end of the manuscript). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each. </p>
									<p>No catchwords. </p>
									<p>The mansucripts is imperfect at the beginning and at the end, with leaves missing after folio 104, 110, 112, 114, 120. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Some folios are stained and/or damaged (see folio 1, 120).</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="3" ruledLines="28" writtenLines="28">
									<p>Masorah magna occupies three lines in the upper and four lines in the lower margin, where it sometimes forms micrographic patterns (e.g. 25v, 26r). </p>
									<p>Pricking and ruling (with hard-point on the hair side of the folio) are visible. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, main text is punctuated and accentuated, the masorah is unpunctuated.</summary>
